-- Malawi Struggling to Obtain Foreign Credit, Daily Times Reports
-- B y   F r a n k   J o m o
-- 2012-02-07T07:38:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-07/malawi-struggling-to-obtain-foreign-credit-daily-times-reports.html
Malawi’s credit-worthiness among
foreign lenders has declined and it’s struggling to get loans
because of the southern African country’s shortage of foreign
currency, the Daily Times reported.  Companies are taking orders from Malawi on a cash-payment
basis, the Blantyre-based newspaper, citing Winford Masanjala,
director of economic affairs in the Ministry of Finance.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Frank Jomo in Blantyre at 
 fjomo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  